    "id": "Q204",
    "title": "Pilot Privileges/ADM - ‘I Don’t Want to File NASA’",
    "category": "Pilot Privileges/ADM",
    "topic": "ADM - Reporting / Learning Culture",
    "airports": "KSDL (Scottsdale)",
    "aircraft": "Cessna 172",
    "scenario": "You accidentally enter a Class C outer ring without establishing communication. Nothing happens in the moment, but you realize it later. You’re embarrassed and don’t want to “draw attention.”",
    "question": "What’s a responsible next step, and why?",
    "correctAnswer": "I should learn from it immediately: debrief, identify root cause, and consider filing an ASRS (NASA) report promptly. The key goal is safety learning and documenting the event; it’s not a ‘get out of jail free’ card. I also review airspace procedures to prevent recurrence.",
