    "title": "Weather - “VFR Not Recommended” (What It Really Means)",
    "category": "Weather & Services",
    "topic": "Weather - Advisory Language and Decision Making",
    "airports": "KDSM (Des Moines) → KALO (Waterloo)",
    "aircraft": "Cessna 172",
    "scenario": "You call Flight Service (or read a briefing) and see “**VFR not recommended**” along your route due to widespread MVFR ceilings expected, with patchy IFR.\n\nYour friend says, “That’s just a suggestion. If we’re legal under 91.155, we can go.”",
    "question": "How should you treat “VFR not recommended,” and what’s your plan?",
