    "trapReasoning": "“Advisories don’t matter. Regulations are the only real standard.”",
    "whyThisMatters": "“VFR not recommended” is essentially a risk label based on experience: conditions may be legal at times and places but still unsafe due to rapid changes, low ceilings, and poor route options. It’s a cue to avoid normalizing marginal conditions, especially for training-level pilots.",
    "cramMode": "“VFR not recommended” means the environment is primed to trap VFR pilots. Legal pockets don’t equal safe margins—avoid or delay.",
