    "aircraft": "Cessna 172",
    "scenario": "Forecast shows scattered showers and ceilings lowering later. You say, “If Athens goes down, I’ll just divert somewhere.”\n\nYour DPE asks, “Where exactly, and what’s your decision point?”",
    "question": "What’s a good answer?",
    "correctAnswer": "A good answer is specific: I identify at least 2–3 alternates with longer runways and services, check their forecast trends, and pick a point in the flight where I commit to divert/return if the trend is worse than expected. I also plan the fuel so the divert isn’t “theoretical.” Alternates aren’t vibes — they’re locations with weather/runway/performance compatibility.",
    "trapReasoning": "“VFR doesn’t require an alternate, so I don’t need to plan one.”",
