    "question": "What do you do with the mixture for takeoff at high density altitude, and why?",
    "correctAnswer": "At high density altitude, the mixture can be overly rich and reduce power. I follow the POH procedure to lean for maximum RPM (or maximum power) during runup/takeoff configuration when appropriate for a normally aspirated engine. The goal is best power, not “full rich by habit.” If I’m unsure, I consult the POH and ask an instructor — but I don’t ignore the power loss risk.",
    "trapReasoning": "“Full rich is always safest. Leaning on the ground is dangerous and unnecessary.”",
